## Context

RDJ-26561 R&R (tracker 0274), remark ED-04. Editor: give the Zenodo package
more structure so readers can distinguish raw data inputs (e.g.
`bibcnrs_works.csv`) from the final data products of this paper
(`climate_finance_corpus.csv`, `embeddings.npz`, `citations.csv`).

## Relevant files

- `build/` archive scripts (`build_*_archive.sh`) and `build/templates/` —
  Phase-4 packaging that produces the deposit
- Zenodo deposit record (see track folder
  `~/CNRS/papiers/sent/RDJ4HSS_Curated_Corpus_Climate_Finance/2026-03-26 Zenodo/`)
- `deliverables/data-paper/data-paper.qmd` — Related dataset / Data sections
  referencing the DOI and package layout

## Actions

1. Restructure the package layout (e.g. `inputs/` vs `products/`
   subdirectories, or clearly sectioned README + manifest) in the Phase-4
   build scripts, so the structure is reproducible, not hand-arranged.
2. Publish a new Zenodo version (new version DOI; concept DOI stable) —
   uploading is the author's call; prepare everything up to the upload.
3. Update the package description/README and the paper's references to the
   package layout accordingly (coordinate with 0279's codebook decision).

## Test

- Archive build script produces the new layout deterministically.

## Verification

- [ ] Rebuilt package tree shows the raw-vs-product split
- [ ] Paper text matches the new layout

## Invariants

- Phase 4 reads Phase 2/3 outputs only; deposit content stays pipeline-traceable.

## Exit criteria

- [ ] New package structure built and staged for Zenodo versioning
- [ ] Response-letter bullet drafted (feeds 0283)
